    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-26T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-26T11:00:00-05:00" n="358"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.11L5232/523: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-26T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 26, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 26—2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>32. Department’s 15, February 21, 6 p.m. Foreign Office states that sabotage
                    evidence, hitherto delayed owing to need for careful analysis by reason of
                    inaccuracy of witnesses, is being hurried and promises <pb facs="0555" n="479"
                        xml:id="pg_479"/> that instructions together with the first section of the
                    evidence will be forwarded to the German Embassy through which channel only it
                    prefers to act by middle of next week,<note n="32" xml:id="d358fn32">By telegram
                        No. 41, March 6, 1935, 4 p.m., the Ambassador in Germany informed the
                        Department that the instructions had been sent to the German Embassy.</note>
                    the final section following soon after.</p>
                <p>Embassy will be informed immediately instructions referred to are sent. I will
                    cable Department. Mail report follows.<note n="33" xml:id="d358fn33">Despatch
                        No. 1813, February 28, 1935, not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodd</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
